raw_data.title: Director
raw_data.description: A Director provides strategic guidance and executive-level oversight and management of multiple, highly complex programs and projects. Requires expert knowledge of federal policies, terminology, operations, and procedures, navigating ambiguity to establish initiative structure, and ensuring delivery of high-quality services. Develops strategy, operating models, methodology and solutions.    Responsible for overall engagement management such as planning and budgeting, defining needs for deliverable content, interacting with executive-level leaders to ensure buy-in on proposed solutions, and monitoring/identifying/escalating potential risks. Responsible for project reviews and overall contract progress and performance. Reviews deliverables and integrates service quality processes throughout the engagement.  Experience typically includes, but may not be limited to, one or more of the following areas: strategic program management, acquisition and contract management, program assessments, service delivery transformation, organizational design, business process reengineering, business process documentation, talent strategy, technology implementation and deployment, data analysis and analytics, survey design and analysis, financial/cost analysis, change management, strategic communications, stakeholder readiness, employee and customer experience, and facilitation.

raw_data.title: Senior Manager
raw_data.description: A Senior Manager provides strategic client engagement and delivery support, and coordinates with team leads to ensure efficient and effective execution of highly complex programs and projects. Requires expert knowledge of federal policies, terminology, operations, and procedures, navigating ambiguity to establish initiative structure, and ensuring delivery of high-quality services.   Responsible for managing and advising program/project team members and serving as the designated client point of contact to facilitate daily operations. Responsible for shaping solutions and adapting delivery based on program/project developments and changes. Responsible for project reviews and overall contract progress, performance, and compliance. Reviews deliverables and integrates service quality processes throughout the engagement.  Experience typically includes, but may not be limited to, one or more of the following areas: strategic program management, acquisition and contract management, program assessments, service delivery transformation, organizational design, business process reengineering, business process documentation, talent strategy, technology implementation and deployment, data analysis and analytics, survey design and analysis, financial/cost analysis, change management, strategic communications, stakeholder readiness, employee and customer experience, and facilitation.

raw_data.title: Manager

Responsible for operating multiple workstreams and stakeholders, managing team members, resource planning and work assignments, identifying next steps, escalating issues, and recommending tools/methodologies to support execution. Responsible for working directly with client leadership and facilitating client meetings and working sessions. Responsible for applying quality assurance practices in development and review of deliverables and work products.   Experience typically includes, but may not be limited to, one or more of the following areas: strategic program management, acquisition and contract management, program assessments, service delivery transformation, organizational design, business process reengineering, business process documentation, talent strategy, technology implementation and deployment, data analysis and analytics, survey design and analysis, financial/cost analysis, change management, strategic communications, stakeholder readiness, employee and customer experience, and facilitation.
